---
// Interactive free-recoil calculator. Vanilla JS, no framework.
// Astro hoists the <script> into a small bundle scoped to pages that import this.
---
<section class="recoil-calc" data-recoil-calc>
  <div class="recoil-calc-head">
    <div class="recoil-calc-kicker">Try your own load</div>
    <h3>Free recoil calculator</h3>
    <p>
      Plug in your bullet weight, target Power Factor, charge, gas factor, and gun
      weight. Computes muzzle velocity from PF, the bullet/gas momentum split, free-recoil
      velocity (V<sub>gun</sub>), and free-recoil energy. Math runs in your browser; no
      data leaves the page.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="recoil-calc-body">
    <div class="recoil-calc-inputs">
      <label class="rc-row">
        <span class="rc-lbl">Bullet weight</span>
        <input type="number" data-input="bullet" value="95" min="60" max="200" step="1" inputmode="decimal" />
        <span class="rc-unit">gr</span>
      </label>
      <label class="rc-row">
        <span class="rc-lbl">Target Power Factor</span>
        <input type="number" data-input="pf" value="130" min="100" max="180" step="1" inputmode="decimal" />
        <span class="rc-unit">PF</span>
      </label>
      <label class="rc-row">
        <span class="rc-lbl">Powder charge</span>
        <input type="number" data-input="charge" value="4.0" min="1" max="10" step="0.1" inputmode="decimal" />
        <span class="rc-unit">gr</span>
      </label>
      <label class="rc-row">
        <span class="rc-lbl">Gas factor (<em>f</em>)</span>
        <input type="number" data-input="f" value="1.0" min="1.0" max="2.0" step="0.05" inputmode="decimal" />
        <span class="rc-unit">×</span>
      </label>
      <label class="rc-row">
        <span class="rc-lbl">Gun weight</span>
        <input type="number" data-input="gun" value="7.5" min="1.5" max="15" step="0.1" inputmode="decimal" />
        <span class="rc-unit">lb</span>
      </label>
    </div>

    <div class="recoil-calc-out">
      <div class="rc-out-row">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Muzzle velocity</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="velocity">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Bullet momentum</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="bullet-momentum">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">gr·fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Gas exit speed (V<sub>gas</sub>)</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="gas-velocity">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Gas momentum</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="gas-momentum">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">gr·fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row total">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Total recoil momentum</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="total-momentum">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">gr·fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row primary">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Recoil velocity (V<sub>gun</sub>)</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="v-gun">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">fps</span>
      </div>
      <div class="rc-out-row primary">
        <span class="rc-out-lbl">Free recoil energy</span>
        <span class="rc-out-val" data-output="energy">—</span>
        <span class="rc-out-unit">ft·lb</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recoil-calc-bar">
    <div class="rc-bar-label">
      <span class="bar-legend-bullet">
        Bullet <span data-output="bullet-pct">—</span>
      </span>
      <span class="bar-legend-gas" data-gas-band="green">
        Gas <span data-output="gas-pct">—</span>
      </span>
    </div>
    <div class="rc-bar-track">
      <div class="rc-bar-bullet" data-bar="bullet"></div>
      <div class="rc-bar-gas" data-bar="gas" data-gas-band="green"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recoil-calc-notes">
    <details open>
      <summary>About the gas factor</summary>
      <p>
        The gas factor <em>f</em> multiplies muzzle velocity to estimate how fast the gas
        column itself exits. Rough anchors: <strong>≈ 1.0</strong> for fast powder fully
        expanded in a 13″+ barrel · <strong>≈ 1.5</strong> SAAMI handgun default ·
        <strong>≈ 1.8</strong> for slow powder still pressurized at the muzzle. The gas
        bar shifts green → amber → red as the factor rises — it visualizes how much of
        your recoil is gas push, not bullet push.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>Where's "burn rate"?</summary>
      <p>
        It's already in the calculator — just split across two inputs, because burn rate
        affects recoil through two independent quantities the equation cares about:
        <strong>charge weight</strong> (mass of powder burned) and the
        <strong>gas factor</strong> (how fast that mass exits the muzzle). Fast powders
        need less charge AND finish burning early enough that gas has room to expand,
        lowering the gas factor. Slow powders need more charge AND are still pressurized
        at the muzzle, raising it. Reaching for AutoComp vs. Longshot at the same PF
        means dialing both inputs in the same direction. There's no single "burn rate"
        knob because the equation doesn't have one — the PCC Recoil Physics article walks
        through the same load with three different (charge, gas factor) pairs to make
        this concrete.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details>
      <summary>What about OAL, position sensitivity, and case volume?</summary>
      <p>
        These don't appear because free recoil is purely a momentum calculation —
        mass × velocity, summed for bullet and gas, divided by gun mass. Seating
        depth, case capacity (Federal vs. Starline vs. Win), powder column orientation,
        primer choice — these change <strong>peak pressure, ignition consistency,
        and standard deviation</strong>, not the first-order recoil momentum coming out
        the back. A 4.0 gr charge produces 4.0 × V<sub>gas</sub> of gas momentum
        regardless of which end of the case it ignited from. They matter enormously for
        load development (9mm is uniquely sensitive — ~8–15% pressure rise per 0.010″
        deeper at near-max charges, per the SAAMI-acknowledged small case volume) but
        they're a different question from "how hard does the gun kick." Use a reloading
        manual and a chronograph for those; use this calculator for the recoil math once
        you've validated the load.
      </p>
    </details>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  type Bands = 'green' | 'amber' | 'red';

  function setup(root: HTMLElement) {
    const $ = <T extends Element = HTMLElement>(sel: string) =>
      root.querySelector(sel) as T | null;
    const $$ = (sel: string) => Array.from(root.querySelectorAll(sel)) as HTMLElement[];

    const inputs = {
      bullet: $<HTMLInputElement>('[data-input="bullet"]')!,
      pf:     $<HTMLInputElement>('[data-input="pf"]')!,
      charge: $<HTMLInputElement>('[data-input="charge"]')!,
      f:      $<HTMLInputElement>('[data-input="f"]')!,
      gun:    $<HTMLInputElement>('[data-input="gun"]')!,
    };

    const out = (name: string) => $<HTMLElement>(`[data-output="${name}"]`)!;
    const outputs = {
      velocity:        out('velocity'),
      bulletMomentum:  out('bullet-momentum'),
      gasVelocity:     out('gas-velocity'),
      gasMomentum:     out('gas-momentum'),
      totalMomentum:   out('total-momentum'),
      vGun:            out('v-gun'),
      energy:          out('energy'),
      bulletPct:       out('bullet-pct'),
      gasPct:          out('gas-pct'),
    };

    const bars = {
      bullet: $<HTMLElement>('[data-bar="bullet"]')!,
      gas:    $<HTMLElement>('[data-bar="gas"]')!,
    };
    const gasBandTargets = $$('[data-gas-band]');

    const fmt = (n: number, d = 0) =>
      Number.isFinite(n)
        ? new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: d, maximumFractionDigits: d }).format(n)
        : '—';

    function band(f: number): Bands {
      if (f <= 1.2) return 'green';
      if (f <= 1.6) return 'amber';
      return 'red';
    }

    function clear() {
      for (const k of Object.keys(outputs) as (keyof typeof outputs)[]) {
        outputs[k].textContent = '—';
      }
      bars.bullet.style.flex = '0 0 50%';
      bars.gas.style.flex = '0 0 50%';
    }

    function compute() {
      const bullet = parseFloat(inputs.bullet.value);
      const pf = parseFloat(inputs.pf.value);
      const charge = parseFloat(inputs.charge.value);
      const f = parseFloat(inputs.f.value);
      const gunLbs = parseFloat(inputs.gun.value);

      if (![bullet, pf, charge, f, gunLbs].every(Number.isFinite) || bullet <= 0 || gunLbs <= 0) {
        clear();
        return;
      }

      const velocity = (pf * 1000) / bullet;          // fps
      const bulletMomentum = bullet * velocity;       // gr·fps
      const vGas = f * velocity;                      // fps
      const gasMomentum = charge * vGas;              // gr·fps
      const totalMomentum = bulletMomentum + gasMomentum;
      const gunGrains = gunLbs * 7000;                // 1 lb = 7000 gr
      const vGun = totalMomentum / gunGrains;         // fps
      const energy = (gunLbs * vGun * vGun) / 64.348; // ft·lb (g = 32.174 fps²)

      const bulletPct = (bulletMomentum / totalMomentum) * 100;
      const gasPct = 100 - bulletPct;

      outputs.velocity.textContent       = fmt(velocity);
      outputs.bulletMomentum.textContent = fmt(bulletMomentum);
      outputs.gasVelocity.textContent    = fmt(vGas);
      outputs.gasMomentum.textContent    = fmt(gasMomentum);
      outputs.totalMomentum.textContent  = fmt(totalMomentum);
      outputs.vGun.textContent           = fmt(vGun, 2);
      outputs.energy.textContent         = fmt(energy, 2);
      outputs.bulletPct.textContent      = fmt(bulletPct, 1) + '%';
      outputs.gasPct.textContent         = fmt(gasPct, 1) + '%';

      bars.bullet.style.flex = `0 0 ${bulletPct}%`;
      bars.gas.style.flex    = `0 0 ${gasPct}%`;

      const b = band(f);
      gasBandTargets.forEach((el) => el.dataset.gasBand = b);
    }

    Object.values(inputs).forEach((el) => el.addEventListener('input', compute));
    compute();
  }

  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-recoil-calc]').forEach(setup);
</script>

<style>
  .recoil-calc {
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 28px 32px;
    margin: 32px 0;
  }
  .recoil-calc-head { margin-bottom: 22px; }
  .recoil-calc-kicker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .recoil-calc h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 22px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-bright);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .recoil-calc p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .recoil-calc-body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  /* INPUTS */
  .recoil-calc-inputs { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
  .rc-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 110px 28px;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .rc-lbl { color: var(--text); }
  .rc-lbl em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); font-family: var(--font-serif); }
  .rc-row input {
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-bright);
    padding: 7px 10px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    text-align: right;
    width: 100%;
    appearance: textfield;
    -moz-appearance: textfield;
  }
  .rc-row input::-webkit-outer-spin-button,
  .rc-row input::-webkit-inner-spin-button {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .rc-row input:focus {
    outline: 1px solid var(--accent);
    outline-offset: -1px;
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  .rc-unit {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  /* OUTPUTS */
  .recoil-calc-out {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--bg-card-alt);
    padding: 12px 16px;
  }
  .rc-out-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 56px;
    gap: 10px;
    padding: 5px 0;
    font-size: 13px;
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .rc-out-lbl { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .rc-out-val {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-bright);
    text-align: right;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .rc-out-unit {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    text-align: left;
  }
  .rc-out-row.total {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-top: 6px;
    padding-top: 9px;
  }
  .rc-out-row.primary .rc-out-val { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

  /* BAR */
  .recoil-calc-bar { margin: 6px 0 18px; }
  .rc-bar-label {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  .bar-legend-bullet { color: var(--text); }
  .bar-legend-gas[data-gas-band="green"] { color: var(--green); }
  .bar-legend-gas[data-gas-band="amber"] { color: var(--accent); }
  .bar-legend-gas[data-gas-band="red"]   { color: var(--red); }

  .rc-bar-track {
    height: 32px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: flex;
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .rc-bar-bullet {
    background: rgba(200, 205, 216, 0.18);
    transition: flex 180ms ease;
  }
  .rc-bar-gas {
    transition: flex 180ms ease, background-color 180ms ease;
  }
  .rc-bar-gas[data-gas-band="green"] { background: var(--green); }
  .rc-bar-gas[data-gas-band="amber"] { background: var(--accent); }
  .rc-bar-gas[data-gas-band="red"]   { background: var(--red); }

  .recoil-calc-notes {
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--border);
    padding-top: 6px;
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes details {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes details:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .recoil-calc-notes summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 12px 0 12px 22px;
    position: relative;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text);
    transition: color 120ms ease;
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes summary:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .recoil-calc-notes summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .recoil-calc-notes summary::before {
    content: '+';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    width: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: transform 150ms ease;
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes details[open] > summary::before {
    content: '−';
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes summary em {
    color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; font-family: var(--font-serif);
    text-transform: none; letter-spacing: 0; font-weight: 400; font-size: 13px;
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes p {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0 4px 16px 22px;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .recoil-calc-notes p em { color: var(--accent); font-style: italic; font-family: var(--font-serif); }
  .recoil-calc-notes p strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .recoil-calc { padding: 22px 18px; }
    .recoil-calc-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 18px; }
    .rc-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 92px 24px; }
    .rc-out-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 50px; gap: 8px; font-size: 12px; }
  }
</style>
